"title": "5717: monogamy",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5717: monogamy",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The practice of having and remaining faithful to only one marriage partner at one time. It is set out as God's ideal for human relationships; an ideal demonstrated in the use of the marriage bond to portray the relationship between God and his people.</p>\n<h2>Monogamy as God's original intention for marriage</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:22-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:22–2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:15\">MAL 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:4-Matt19:6\">MAT 19:4–19:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:6-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:6–10:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31\">EPH 5:31</a></p>\n<h2>Monogamy is shown in God's relationship with his people</h2>\n<h3>God's marriage with Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5-Isa54:8\">ISA 54:5–54:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:2-Jer2:3\">JER 2:2–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:16-Hos2:20\">HOS 2:16–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1\">HOS 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:32-Eph5:33\">EPH 5:32–5:33</a></p>\n<h3>God's exclusive commitment to Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:2\">DEU 14:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:2\">AMO 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:5–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:18\">DEU 26:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:8\">DEU 32:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:4\">PSA 135:4</a></p>\n<h2>Monogamy in marriage</h2>\n<h3>The commitment to a lifelong, loving companionship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:18\">GEN 2:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:15-Prov5:19\">PRO 5:15–5:19</a></strong> <em>The satisfaction that may be found in marriage makes marital unfaithfulness and polygamy unnecessary.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:17\">PRO 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:9\">ECC 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14\">MAL 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Polygamy undermines full commitment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:15\">DEU 21:15</a></strong> <em>Favouritism within polygamous relationships undermines the close companionship which should characterise marriage.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:30\">GEN 29:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:1-1Sam1:8\">1SA 1:1–1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:21-2Chr11:22\">2CH 11:21–11:22</a></p>\n<h2>Monogamy is implicit in teaching about divorce</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:9\">MAT 19:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:11\">MRK 10:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:18\">LUK 16:18</a></p>\n<h2>Monogamy is commanded</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:2-1Cor7:4\">1CO 7:2–7:4</a></strong> <em>This is an implicit, but clear prohibition of polygamy</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:12\">1TI 3:12</a></strong> <em>Monogamy is obligatory in leaders.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:2\">1TI 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:6\">TIT 1:6</a></p>",
